EXE BUILD STEPS FOR TEMPERATURE DASHBOARD (PYQT)

---

STEP 1: INSTALL PYINSTALLER

Open terminal / command prompt and run:

pip install pyinstaller

---

STEP 2: GO TO PROJECT FOLDER

cd path\to\your\project

Example:
cd C:\Users\Rishi\Desktop\project

---

STEP 3: CHECK PROJECT RUNS

Run:

python main.py

Make sure:

- UI opens
- Graphs are visible
- No errors

---

STEP 4: FIX LOG DIRECTORY (IMPORTANT)

In your code, replace:

LOG_DIR = "C:/DGS/log"

With:

import os
LOG_DIR = os.path.join(os.getcwd(), "log")

Then create a folder:

project/
main.py
log/
(your csv files)

---

STEP 5: BUILD EXE

Run:

pyinstaller --onefile --windowed main.py

---

STEP 6: IF GRAPH NOT SHOWING

Run instead:

pyinstaller --onefile --windowed --hidden-import matplotlib main.py

---

STEP 7: FIND EXE FILE

Go to:

dist/

You will see:

main.exe

---

STEP 8: TEST EXE

Double click:

main.exe

Check:

- UI opens
- Graph updates
- No crash

---

STEP 9: SHARE TO OTHER LAPTOP

Send:

main.exe
log/ folder

OR zip both

---

FINAL RESULT

You now have a standalone Windows application
No Python installation required on other systems

---